# Codencil — AI agent workflow

Before writing code, read the docs in **`agents/`** (in order):

1. [`agents/CONTEXT.md`](agents/CONTEXT.md) — orientation
2. [`agents/progress.md`](agents/progress.md) — open stack + next task
3. [`agents/STACK.md`](agents/STACK.md) — **check open PRs**; resume from `main` or stack tip
4. [`agents/AGENTS.md`](agents/AGENTS.md) — rules & defaults
5. [`agents/BUILD_ORDER.md`](agents/BUILD_ORDER.md) — task deliverables & verify steps
6. [`agents/DECISIONS.md`](agents/DECISIONS.md) — when unsure *why*

## Session rules

- **First:** `gh pr list --state open` — no open PRs → branch from `main`; else branch from **tip of stack** (see `STACK.md`)
- Execute **exactly one** `BUILD_ORDER` task ID per session (e.g. `P0.1`)
- **Stacked PRs:** open ready for review (no draft); see `agents/STACK.md`; **do not merge**
- **CI gate:** `gh pr checks <number>` must pass before starting the next BUILD_ORDER task
- **Update** `agents/progress.md` (checkboxes + open stack table + session log)
- **Do not** re-debate defaults in `AGENTS.md` (chi, MIT, TypRow, dev auth stub)
- **Do not** implement approval gates, OIDC before Phase 4, or TypRow library changes
- Anchors attach to **published version snapshots**, never live draft
- **Docker only** — no local Go/Node/migrate; build, test, run via `docker compose` (P0.2)

## Stack

Go (**chi** v5) + Postgres + go-migrate + TypRow + Next.js (`apps/web`). All tooling in Docker. Markdown renders client-side only.
